   <p class="auto-cursor-target">v2 Description: The IAM segment contains person/patient adverse reaction information of various types.  Each IAM segment describes a single person/patient adverse reaction.  </p>
   <p>
      <span style="color: rgb(51,51,51);">FHIR Description (AllergyIntolerance): <span style="color: rgb(51,51,51);">Risk of harmful or undesirable, physiological response which is unique to an individual and associated with exposure to a substance.</span>
      </span>
   </p>
   <p>
      <br/>
   </p>
   <p>The v2 description of IAMindicates that each "IAM segment describes a single person/patient adverse reaction". This could be interpreted to mean that a given message may have multiple IAM segments with the same allergen code in IAM-3. That is, if a single patient was exposed to the same allergen twice (and maybe even had a different reaction each time (rash the first time and anaphylaxis the second time)), there would potentially be multiple IAM segments, one for each exposure. In that case, a single AllergyIntolerance resource would be created from multiple IAM segments and with mulitple AllergyIntolerance.reaction elements. Does this match real life experience with IAM segments?</p>
